item.description:
@krackkid wrote:

[quote=“The Reaper X, post:29, topic:340793”][quote author=krackkid link=topic=437179.msg3216732#msg3216732 date=1274740515]

[quote author=The Reaper X link=topic=437179.msg3216728#msg3216728 date=1274740440]

I have, rollerstaked, skateboarded, BMX, snowboard, sandboard, and windsurf, I would have to say the hardest is sandboarding…

Sandboarding - You need a skateboard without wheels/a normal snowboard, and nice sand dunes, which where I used to live here in Florida had alot of them.
[/quote]What’s hard about sandboarding? You just slide down a hill.

Lol, idk its just the hardest one to me. I normally end up flipping becuase I hit something wrong.
[/quote]Lool, snowboarding is extremely hard. Well, for the first time anyways. I was expecting it to be like skateboarding, but it turned out to be entirely different.[/quote]
Same here, when I first skateboarded I was like man, this is easy…I tried sandboarding/snowboarding, and was like WTF lol…
